{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17649678","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17649678"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:06:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:06:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18374"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18374","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18374"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.56,0.11,0.11,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11092"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74670"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11092","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11092"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18374"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60153"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25720"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25723"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25842"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74670","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74670"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 57-year-old man presents with a problem in his left leg which is eventually confirmed to be a deep venous thrombosis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"With which one of the following symptoms did he most likely present?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Coldness","Erythema","Pallor","Numbness","Cyanosis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDeep vein thrombosis is a condition where a blood clot forms in a deep vein, usually in the legs. It can lead to significant complications if not identified and managed appropriately.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe most common symptom associated with deep vein thrombosis is \u003Cstrong\u003Eerythema\u003C/strong\u003E, which is redness of the skin over the affected area. This occurs due to inflammation and increased blood flow to the area. Other common symptoms include swelling, warmth, and pain in the affected limb.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EColdness\u003C/strong\u003E - This is more indicative of arterial insufficiency rather than venous thrombosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPallor\u003C/strong\u003E - This is not typically associated with deep vein thrombosis and may suggest arterial issues.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENumbness\u003C/strong\u003E - While discomfort is common, numbness is not a primary symptom of deep vein thrombosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECyanosis\u003C/strong\u003E - This is a late sign and not commonly seen in early or uncomplicated deep vein thrombosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Deep vein thrombosis often presents with erythema, swelling, and warmth in the affected limb.","Coldness is not a typical feature of deep vein thrombosis and may suggest arterial insufficiency instead.","Deep vein thrombosis can lead to complications such as pulmonary embolism if not treated promptly."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Smith, R., \u0026 Wordsworth, P. (2016). Oxford textbook of clinical and biochemical disorders of the skeleton. Oxford University Press","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60153"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18374"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60153","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60153"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-26T15:19:21+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-26T15:19:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11092"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74670"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","synonyms":null,"description":"Understand (interpreting and summarizing information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}}